WEBVTT

00:45.380 --> 00:48.047
<i> [tense music]</i>

00:48.049 --> 00:50.182
- Move it! Move it!
- Move!

00:50.317 --> 00:53.185
<i> - I was born for battle.</i>

00:53.320 --> 00:55.121
<i> Built for it.</i>

00:56.257 --> 00:58.924
<i> Sometimes in battle,</i>
<i> a perfectly crafted plan</i>

00:58.926 --> 01:01.194
<i> gets compromised.</i>

01:01.328 --> 01:04.196
<i> A true general comes up</i>
<i> with a better one</i>

01:04.331 --> 01:06.732
<i> right there on the spot,</i>

01:06.867 --> 01:10.335
<i> working without a net</i>

01:10.337 --> 01:14.740
<i> and sticking the landing</i>
<i> to thunderous applause.</i>

01:14.742 --> 01:16.609
- [panting]

01:19.280 --> 01:22.415
- Hurry up, you dogs!
Let's go! Let's go!

01:22.549 --> 01:27.920
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:29.757 --> 01:30.956
- Where are they?

01:30.958 --> 01:32.425
- They were coming
straight at us

01:32.559 --> 01:33.959
and then veered away
on a sidetrack.

01:33.961 --> 01:35.428
This line bends Southwest.

01:35.562 --> 01:37.763
At that speed, they could be
20 kilometers away by now.

01:37.898 --> 01:39.765
- Or coming about
to nip at our heels.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.166
- I'm sorry, sir.
There was no warning.

01:41.302 --> 01:43.035
- No, they saw to that,
didn't they?

01:43.170 --> 01:45.771
No satellite coverage.
A moonless night.

01:45.906 --> 01:47.239
An ambush from the shadows!

01:47.374 --> 01:48.841
- As cowardly as the day
they left, sir.

01:48.976 --> 01:51.110
- No, they didn't drive by
for nothing.

01:51.112 --> 01:52.778
[alarms beeping]

01:52.913 --> 01:54.647
Forward lamps to full.

01:54.782 --> 01:57.116
[machinery whirs]

01:57.118 --> 01:58.583
Brake!

01:58.585 --> 02:00.853
[brakes screech]

02:00.988 --> 02:04.523
<i> There's a moment in a fight</i>
<i> when that first blow lands</i>

02:04.525 --> 02:06.925
<i> and everything stops.</i>

02:06.927 --> 02:09.662
<i> And in that flash of clarity,</i>

02:09.797 --> 02:11.264
<i> you know who you are.</i>

02:12.733 --> 02:17.270
<i> I'll push as hard as it takes</i>
<i> to get my engine back.</i>

02:17.404 --> 02:22.074
<i> Snowpiercer, 1,023 cars long.</i>

02:22.209 --> 02:25.077
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

02:25.212 --> 02:32.084
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:40.027 --> 02:42.027
Full thrust. Push through it.

02:42.029 --> 02:44.563
- Sir, if that axel--
- Full power, Engineer. Now!

02:44.699 --> 02:46.832
[metal clanking]

02:46.834 --> 02:48.301
[sparks crackling]

02:48.435 --> 02:51.604
[engine whirring]

02:53.574 --> 02:56.175
- Well done, sir.
Round one to you.

02:56.177 --> 02:59.378
- No, no, that trap
wasn't meant to stop us.

02:59.514 --> 03:00.846
It was meant to slow us down.

03:00.982 --> 03:02.715
We can't have
any setbacks today, Kevin.

03:02.850 --> 03:04.317
Ruth's people
will be energized.

03:04.451 --> 03:05.518
Find them.

03:05.652 --> 03:06.852
- I know just where to start.

03:06.988 --> 03:10.723
- Take the gloves off.
Make an example.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.659
- I thought you'd never ask.

03:14.996 --> 03:17.129
- And Kevin?
- Yes, sir.

03:18.665 --> 03:19.798
- Send Zarah to me.

03:19.800 --> 03:22.201
<i> [dark, atmospheric music]</i>

03:22.203 --> 03:23.468
What's our speed?

03:23.604 --> 03:25.271
- 14 kilometers an hour.

03:26.341 --> 03:29.675
- All right, Mr. Layton,
you got us at a crawl.

03:29.677 --> 03:31.276
What's the play?

03:31.412 --> 03:34.279
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:34.415 --> 03:36.949
Layton knows better
than to connect end to end.

03:37.084 --> 03:40.085
My Jackboots would just
sweep in and crush him.

03:40.221 --> 03:43.622
So he's going to peck at us
from the side.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.024
- He needs parallel track.

03:45.026 --> 03:48.160
- And this rail yard
is an entire maze of it.

03:48.295 --> 03:53.966
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:54.101 --> 03:55.434
- [gasps]

03:55.570 --> 03:58.437
<i> [tense music]</i>

03:58.573 --> 04:03.842
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:03.978 --> 04:06.645
He broke free of the snare
but slowed down.

04:06.647 --> 04:08.581
- We can get
right up alongside him

04:08.716 --> 04:09.782
in these sidings.

04:09.917 --> 04:12.051
They'll be in position
in 2 kilometers.

04:12.053 --> 04:13.786
- Bring us around, Ben.
- Copy that.

04:13.921 --> 04:15.320
- How long we got?
- Three, four minutes.

04:15.456 --> 04:17.522
- All right, stay sharp.
Let's get this done.

04:17.524 --> 04:19.792
I'll make sure Josie's ready.

04:22.263 --> 04:23.862
- Bess.

04:23.864 --> 04:26.865
♪ Bess Till ♪

04:26.867 --> 04:29.735
♪ Bess! ♪
- Audrey, shut it.

04:29.737 --> 04:32.738
- What's happening? Is it him?

04:32.740 --> 04:35.674
- You'll know it's him
when his head is on a pike.

04:35.676 --> 04:38.411
- [gasps]
Oh.

04:38.545 --> 04:43.682
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:43.684 --> 04:45.751
- You ready for this?

04:45.753 --> 04:47.486
- Ben takes us close.
I jump over,

04:47.488 --> 04:49.755
breach the Big Alice engine,
and you reconnect.

04:50.625 --> 04:52.024
- We only get one shot at it.

04:52.159 --> 04:55.360
- Well, then,
better not miss it.

04:55.496 --> 05:02.401
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:21.388 --> 05:24.256
- Zarah, just in time.

05:24.391 --> 05:25.791
Thought you should
be here for this.

05:25.926 --> 05:27.793
- As a hostage or a spectator?

05:27.795 --> 05:30.195
- As my confidante,
nothing less.

05:30.331 --> 05:32.832
Come. Come on.

05:35.470 --> 05:36.836
Have a look.

05:38.072 --> 05:43.342
See, that's your old life
creeping up our flank.

05:43.478 --> 05:45.744
- Are they attacking?

05:45.880 --> 05:48.281
- Maybe they're here
to surrender.

05:48.415 --> 05:50.216
You see any white flags?

05:52.487 --> 05:54.553
- No.
- No.

05:54.555 --> 05:56.355
No, and if I had to guess,

05:56.491 --> 05:59.958
I'd say they're trying
to cut the head off the snake.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.627
But I have a surprise for them.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.363
<i> [dark, atmospheric music]</i>

06:04.365 --> 06:07.233
- [grunting]

06:09.770 --> 06:11.170
- Heave.

06:13.308 --> 06:14.773
Heave.

06:14.775 --> 06:18.844
- Well, whatever these tin cans
are for can't be good.

06:18.846 --> 06:21.646
- Pike, man, what's the plan?

06:21.648 --> 06:24.116
[both grunting]

06:24.251 --> 06:25.450
- Keep your eyes on your work.

06:25.586 --> 06:27.786
- Heave.
- And quit standing around!

06:27.788 --> 06:29.188
Let's go.

06:29.190 --> 06:31.256
- Come on. What are you doing?

06:31.258 --> 06:33.658
- All right, time to move.
I'll distract them.

06:33.660 --> 06:35.060
You guys get to Ruth.

06:35.196 --> 06:37.530
- No. Whoa, whoa.
That's not how it works, man.

06:37.665 --> 06:40.733
You're in charge now.
You don't get caught.

06:40.868 --> 06:43.936
[indistinct chatter]

06:44.071 --> 06:46.372
<i> - Hei, húndàn.</i>

06:47.408 --> 06:49.141
Catch.
[grunts]

06:49.276 --> 06:51.744
<i> [tense music]</i>

06:51.879 --> 06:54.747
[grunting]

06:54.882 --> 06:59.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:59.687 --> 07:01.487
[grunting]

07:03.624 --> 07:06.692
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

07:06.694 --> 07:09.695
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:09.697 --> 07:11.397
- We're in position.

07:13.500 --> 07:15.701
[monitor beeps]

07:15.703 --> 07:18.837
- Josie, it's time.
Be careful out there.

07:18.973 --> 07:21.374
- I'll breach the bastard,
don't worry.

07:21.508 --> 07:22.575
[alarm blaring]

07:22.710 --> 07:24.109
[breathing heavily]

07:24.111 --> 07:27.112
- [grunting]

07:27.114 --> 07:29.382
Now! Harpoon!
- Deploy.

07:29.516 --> 07:33.919
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:33.921 --> 07:35.788
- Opening cold-lock.

07:35.923 --> 07:38.591
[breathing heavily]

07:38.726 --> 07:40.393
[alarm blaring]

07:40.527 --> 07:46.599
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:46.734 --> 07:48.200
Wilford has a cannon
or something.

07:48.335 --> 07:50.135
Pull back!
- Switch track.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.737
Josie, hold on.

07:51.872 --> 07:57.076
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:57.211 --> 08:00.346
[metal screeching]

08:02.549 --> 08:04.951
- We're derailing!
- Try to stabilize.

08:06.020 --> 08:07.954
- Well done.

08:10.891 --> 08:12.557
Never fails to amaze me.

08:12.559 --> 08:15.560
You take so much in
and give so little back.

08:15.562 --> 08:20.032
I just hobbled your man, Zarah,
and you didn't even flinch.

08:23.704 --> 08:27.874
At this rate, the war will be
over by daybreak.

08:30.177 --> 08:32.945
[metal creaking]

08:34.048 --> 08:39.584
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:39.586 --> 08:41.921
- Come on. The car is damaged.
We gotta go.

08:42.056 --> 08:43.656
Let's go.

08:44.792 --> 08:46.391
- We have to cut it loose.
It's gonna derail us.

08:46.393 --> 08:47.860
- Cut here? That's four cars.

08:47.995 --> 08:50.195
- It's the closest J-link.
It's the only option.

08:50.197 --> 08:52.298
- Asha's back there.
- We don't have time.

08:53.868 --> 08:55.000
- Go.

08:55.136 --> 08:56.469
- You okay? Thank you.

08:56.604 --> 08:58.137
- She waited
eight years outside.

08:58.273 --> 08:59.639
Can't very well kill her
on day two.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.675
- Safety's off.

09:02.810 --> 09:06.145
[rumbling]

09:06.147 --> 09:08.213
- Disconnecting now

09:08.349 --> 09:11.016
[monitors beep]

09:11.152 --> 09:12.751
And we're clear.

09:12.753 --> 09:15.922
[metal creaking]

09:20.828 --> 09:22.395
- Here.

09:26.834 --> 09:28.301
You'll be safer up here.

09:31.772 --> 09:33.272
Hey...

09:34.909 --> 09:36.576
You gonna be okay?

09:39.981 --> 09:41.647
- Turn out the lights.

09:44.118 --> 09:45.651
- Sure.

09:48.523 --> 09:49.989
Hold fast, okay?

09:49.991 --> 09:52.992
<i> [dark music]</i>

09:52.994 --> 10:00.166
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:01.736 --> 10:04.237
- [exhales shakily]

10:16.017 --> 10:19.552
[breathing echoes]

10:24.225 --> 10:30.162
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:30.297 --> 10:32.297
[monitors beeping]

10:32.433 --> 10:34.299
- We have a problem.

10:34.435 --> 10:37.236
Wilford's gone.

10:37.372 --> 10:40.373
His train went dark.
He could be anywhere now.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.980
- Switch off comms
and transmitters tip to tail.

10:48.115 --> 10:49.648
Not a peep.

10:49.784 --> 10:53.652
[keys clacking]

10:53.788 --> 10:56.521
Zarah, what are you doing
still on your feet?

10:56.523 --> 10:59.091
You must be exhausted.
Come.

11:02.197 --> 11:04.663
- So what are you planning?

11:04.799 --> 11:05.864
- [exhales sharply]

11:06.000 --> 11:07.733
Bit of a lull.

11:07.868 --> 11:09.468
It'll do us good.

11:12.673 --> 11:14.473
Catch our breath.

11:14.609 --> 11:17.342
I've invested a lot in you.

11:17.344 --> 11:19.945
And the child.

11:20.081 --> 11:22.081
I just want to keep you
near me,

11:22.216 --> 11:23.883
for your protection.

11:24.018 --> 11:27.753
- And because they won't attack
the engine if I'm in it.

11:27.888 --> 11:29.555
- Right.

11:31.826 --> 11:39.065
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:45.940 --> 11:47.406
- How do you lose
a 10-mile train?

11:47.542 --> 11:49.008
- We were the ones
that led him into this maze.

11:49.143 --> 11:50.409
- He could be running.

11:50.545 --> 11:51.944
These six routes head
out of the valley.

11:52.079 --> 11:53.746
If he gets to linear track,
we'll lose our advantage.

11:53.881 --> 11:55.348
- Yeah, or he's around
the next corner,

11:55.482 --> 11:56.615
laying in wait.

11:56.751 --> 11:58.684
- He's gonna pick us off
piece by piece.

11:58.686 --> 12:00.485
I looked into the muzzle
of that thing.

12:00.621 --> 12:02.555
- We need to get eyes on him.
Can we get to higher ground?

12:02.690 --> 12:04.623
- Here, track follows
the ridgeline.

12:04.625 --> 12:06.225
Should give us a view
of the whole basin.

12:06.361 --> 12:08.227
- Okay, let's do it.
Lights out.

12:08.229 --> 12:10.029
If he's gonna go dark,
so do we.

12:10.031 --> 12:12.765
<i> [intense music]</i>

12:12.900 --> 12:19.438
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:20.375 --> 12:22.241
- Up and at 'em, lovebirds.

12:22.243 --> 12:23.442
- Kevin!

12:23.578 --> 12:25.644
Get out. How dare you?

12:25.646 --> 12:28.181
- Commandeering the Nightcar.
- Ugh, Kevin.

12:28.315 --> 12:29.448
- On whose authority?

12:29.584 --> 12:33.318
- Call it a wartime measure.

12:33.320 --> 12:35.854
Oh, you didn't hear?
Layton's back.

12:35.990 --> 12:38.591
Up. There's work to do.

12:39.927 --> 12:45.731
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:45.866 --> 12:48.768
[indistinct chatter]

12:54.275 --> 12:57.476
- [chuckles]

12:58.879 --> 13:02.248
- Why don't you, um,
go put some coffee on?

13:14.028 --> 13:15.628
- Who--who's there?

13:15.763 --> 13:18.363
- Here to see the prisoner.

13:18.499 --> 13:19.765
I'm her lawyer.

13:19.900 --> 13:22.101
- I don't think
that's a thing anymore.

13:22.236 --> 13:24.437
- Lose your helmet, Jackboot?

13:24.571 --> 13:27.640
- Hey, come on, man. Hey.

13:27.775 --> 13:29.708
- Do you know me?

13:29.710 --> 13:32.311
- You're--you're a Tailie.

13:32.313 --> 13:34.379
Forgive me,
I-I don't know your name.

13:34.381 --> 13:36.649
- I know you.

13:36.784 --> 13:38.183
Whiggins.

13:38.319 --> 13:39.918
- Yes.

13:39.920 --> 13:42.855
- Well, there's two things
you should know about Tailies.

13:42.990 --> 13:46.659
We have long memories
and we win wars.

13:46.794 --> 13:49.394
- Oh, yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

13:49.396 --> 13:50.930
We won the last one.

13:51.065 --> 13:52.665
And we'll win this one.

13:52.800 --> 13:56.401
And do you wanna be the guy
who stands in the way?

13:56.537 --> 13:58.971
Hmm, Whiggins?

14:01.608 --> 14:03.609
- You have ten minutes,
Counselor.

14:03.744 --> 14:05.945
Let me just get
the door for you.

14:06.080 --> 14:08.080
[beeping]

14:08.215 --> 14:09.749
[clears throat]

14:14.489 --> 14:16.621
- Pike?
- You're looking good, girl,

14:16.623 --> 14:18.023
with those arms dangling down.

14:18.025 --> 14:20.025
- You shouldn't be here.
It's too dangerous.

14:20.027 --> 14:21.694
- I'm gonna get you
out of here.

14:21.829 --> 14:23.428
- Wait, wait, wait.
Tell me what happened.

14:23.430 --> 14:25.831
- Wilford drove Layton off
with cannon fire.

14:25.833 --> 14:28.100
Now we're rolling around
in the dark.

14:29.103 --> 14:31.904
- Well, if Wilford is hiding,
then we need to signal Layton.

14:32.039 --> 14:34.773
- I'm gonna get you
out of here first.

14:34.909 --> 14:35.774
- You can't.

14:35.776 --> 14:37.109
You'd have to kill Whiggins,

14:37.244 --> 14:38.511
and then you'd have
to find Clifford

14:38.646 --> 14:41.113
and kill him too,
'cause he's got the keys.

14:41.248 --> 14:43.115
- Go on.

14:43.250 --> 14:47.320
- Pike, Mr. Pike,
you're a dear man

14:47.454 --> 14:51.123
and a brave one,
but this war is bigger than us.

14:51.258 --> 14:54.593
<i> [soft dramatic music]</i>

14:54.729 --> 14:56.629
- How do I signal Layton?

14:59.466 --> 15:00.933
- I've got an idea,

15:01.068 --> 15:03.402
but you'll have to get uptrain
to hospitality.

15:03.404 --> 15:06.405
[breathing echoes]

15:06.407 --> 15:13.346
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:13.480 --> 15:14.947
- [muffled]
Asha.

15:15.082 --> 15:17.816
Hey, you good in there?

15:17.818 --> 15:20.019
I'm sorry, I dropped you
right in the thick of it.

15:20.021 --> 15:21.354
Here.

15:21.488 --> 15:23.222
[normal voice]
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

15:23.224 --> 15:24.489
- What's going on?

15:24.625 --> 15:26.692
Did Mr. Wilford
cripple the train?

15:26.694 --> 15:28.493
- No, look, it's just some
cat and mouse, all right?

15:28.629 --> 15:29.762
It's fine.

15:29.897 --> 15:31.430
- And you're supposed
to be the cat?

15:31.566 --> 15:33.032
Eight of you against
the great Mr. Wilford.

15:33.167 --> 15:35.034
- The great Mr. Wilford
is not who you think he is.

15:35.036 --> 15:36.902
- Isn't he the one
that saved all of you?

15:36.904 --> 15:38.637
- We saved our own damn selves.

15:38.639 --> 15:40.706
He built all of this
just so he could be king.

15:40.841 --> 15:42.174
- So now it's your turn?
- No.

15:42.309 --> 15:43.776
This is personal for us, okay?

15:43.911 --> 15:45.644
I have a partner
that I boarded with.

15:45.646 --> 15:47.580
I have a child on the way.

15:47.715 --> 15:51.050
- Oh, if you're doing this
for a child,

15:51.185 --> 15:54.220
you will do things
that you will regret.

15:55.256 --> 15:58.991
- I just came in to warn you.
We are not giving up.

15:59.126 --> 16:01.994
This is gonna get worse
before it gets better, okay?

16:02.129 --> 16:04.597
- Okay.
- Hold on.

16:04.732 --> 16:11.804
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:13.941 --> 16:17.743
- ♪ You are my sunshine ♪

16:17.745 --> 16:21.680
♪ My only sunshine ♪

16:21.682 --> 16:25.350
♪ You make me happy ♪

16:25.352 --> 16:28.621
♪ When skies are gray ♪

16:28.756 --> 16:32.691
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

16:32.693 --> 16:36.762
♪ How much I love you ♪

16:36.897 --> 16:39.298
♪ Please don't take ♪

16:39.434 --> 16:44.369
♪ My sunshine away ♪

16:44.505 --> 16:47.306
- You know, when you sing,
I can almost convince myself

16:47.442 --> 16:49.975
you're not a horrible person.

16:49.977 --> 16:51.844
- Thank you.

16:51.979 --> 16:54.046
- And then I remember
you only sing covers,

16:54.181 --> 16:56.715
so the words aren't
actually yours.

16:56.717 --> 16:59.584
- Lyrics are just dressing.

16:59.586 --> 17:01.053
I sing for him.

17:01.188 --> 17:03.923
- Oh, God.

17:04.058 --> 17:05.791
- You scoff,

17:05.793 --> 17:09.128
but at the end of the day,
that's all there is.

17:09.130 --> 17:10.930
A person you sing for.

17:18.739 --> 17:21.407
Who's that to you, Bess?

17:26.814 --> 17:29.615
How do you get all the way
to the end of the world

17:29.750 --> 17:32.618
and have no one?

17:32.753 --> 17:35.420
- I have people.

17:35.556 --> 17:37.622
- Who?

17:37.624 --> 17:41.827
- Layton, Zarah, Roche.

17:41.962 --> 17:42.895
- Roche?

17:43.030 --> 17:44.429
- Yeah, Roche.

17:44.565 --> 17:46.765
He was like a mentor to me
and--

17:46.767 --> 17:49.168
and a friend.

17:49.170 --> 17:53.572
Even though I fought him, he--
he had my back.

17:53.574 --> 17:56.209
No, I don't--
I don't sing for him.

17:57.845 --> 17:59.712
But not a day goes by
when I don't think about

17:59.847 --> 18:01.848
getting him
out of those Drawers.

18:04.251 --> 18:05.785
- I'm sorry.

18:08.189 --> 18:09.856
I hope he survived.

18:11.592 --> 18:13.392
- Yeah.

18:13.528 --> 18:16.261
[phone ringing]

18:16.263 --> 18:19.264
<i> [tense music]</i>

18:19.266 --> 18:20.599
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:20.601 --> 18:22.401
<i> - We're at the ridge. Eyes up.</i>

18:23.270 --> 18:25.738
If he is in the valley,
this is the best vantage point.

18:25.873 --> 18:31.811
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:33.480 --> 18:35.614
- Anything?
- Till?

18:35.616 --> 18:38.217
<i> - Negative. There's nothing.</i>
- [sighs]

18:38.353 --> 18:40.485
- But they can't just vanish.

18:40.621 --> 18:47.727
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:13.520 --> 19:15.188
- Time to put on a show.

19:21.862 --> 19:25.130
<i> [soft music]</i>

19:25.132 --> 19:29.134
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:29.270 --> 19:31.470
[monitor beeping]

19:31.606 --> 19:34.139
[distant booming]

19:34.141 --> 19:35.674
- [exhales]

19:35.676 --> 19:42.081
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:42.216 --> 19:43.816
To the south,
far end of the valley.

19:43.951 --> 19:45.818
<i> Are you guys seeing this?</i>

19:45.953 --> 19:48.687
- Oh, my God.
Wait, wait, wait.

19:48.823 --> 19:50.623
Is that--
- Ha.

19:51.492 --> 19:53.192
They're still with us.

19:54.895 --> 19:57.997
[fireworks booming]

20:00.701 --> 20:01.834
- [laughs]

20:01.969 --> 20:03.636
- We see you, Joseph.

20:03.771 --> 20:05.338
- Ha.

20:10.845 --> 20:13.646
- [breathing heavily]

20:13.781 --> 20:16.649
[fireworks booming]

20:16.784 --> 20:20.119
<i> [tense music]</i>

20:23.725 --> 20:24.924
- He's making a break for it.

20:25.059 --> 20:27.059
East over the ridge
to the trunk line.

20:27.194 --> 20:28.660
He wants to sneak out
of the rail yard

20:28.662 --> 20:30.196
because it's where we have
tactical advantage.

20:30.331 --> 20:31.731
- If he gets out of the valley,

20:31.865 --> 20:32.932
he's looking
at days of linear track.

20:33.067 --> 20:35.735
- Can we beat him to it?
- Alex?

20:35.869 --> 20:37.203
- No.

20:37.338 --> 20:39.471
I don't know, maybe.
It's all assumptions.

20:39.473 --> 20:40.940
- What are we waiting for?
Pedal down.

20:41.075 --> 20:42.674
- Let's cut 'em off
at the pass.

20:42.810 --> 20:44.944
<i> [tense music]</i>

20:45.079 --> 20:46.546
- Full throttle, Engineer.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.748
- Sir, with respect,
we're draining really fast.

20:48.882 --> 20:50.750
A few ticks slower
would be more efficient.

20:50.884 --> 20:54.086
- They've seen us.
They're coming!

20:54.088 --> 20:55.687
Tap every last reserve

20:55.823 --> 20:57.557
and get us
over that bloody ridge!

20:57.691 --> 21:00.626
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:00.762 --> 21:03.629
[air hissing]

21:03.765 --> 21:06.698
- [groans]

21:06.834 --> 21:08.834
[screams]

21:08.970 --> 21:10.770
- Come on! What are you doing?

21:10.905 --> 21:13.305
- [pants heavily]

21:13.307 --> 21:15.641
- So you have a choice,
Strong Boy.

21:15.777 --> 21:18.710
I can take two fingers
next time

21:18.712 --> 21:20.379
or I can take your thumb.

21:20.514 --> 21:22.914
Or you could be smart

21:22.916 --> 21:24.049
like when
you bravely volunteered

21:24.185 --> 21:26.452
to step up to my table here.

21:26.587 --> 21:28.654
Wilford just needs you
to start talking

21:28.656 --> 21:31.390
and name your collaborators.

21:31.525 --> 21:33.325
- [breathing heavily]

21:33.461 --> 21:35.595
No.

21:35.729 --> 21:36.862
- No?

21:36.998 --> 21:38.965
- Come on. Leave him alone!

21:40.734 --> 21:42.534
- Hold him.
- Ah, no!

21:42.670 --> 21:43.869
No!

21:43.871 --> 21:45.471
- [panting heavily]

21:45.607 --> 21:47.673
<i> [tense music]</i>

21:47.675 --> 21:49.609
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:49.743 --> 21:51.477
Stop!
[grunts]

21:54.948 --> 21:56.616
- I didn't sign up for this.

21:56.750 --> 21:58.484
Just wanted to serve some
drinks and play some tunes.

21:58.620 --> 22:01.887
- Would you relax?
War is not pretty.

22:02.023 --> 22:04.624
But Wilford will reward us.

22:04.758 --> 22:06.025
- If he wins.

22:06.160 --> 22:08.628
- Of course he'll win.

22:08.762 --> 22:10.229
- If he doesn't?
- [screams]

22:10.364 --> 22:12.431
- And Layton rolls in here,
finds this?

22:12.566 --> 22:14.366
Finds us?

22:14.368 --> 22:16.101
Wilford's little
wedding puppets.

22:16.103 --> 22:17.769
- We're not the torturers,
all right?

22:17.905 --> 22:20.506
We're just providing a venue.

22:20.642 --> 22:23.375
- I'm sure the mutilated guy
will be quick to sort that out.

22:23.377 --> 22:24.644
- Hmm?

22:24.778 --> 22:26.578
Look, if you're not gonna talk,

22:26.714 --> 22:29.649
I guess you don't need
that tongue anymore.

22:29.783 --> 22:31.116
Hold him, please.

22:31.118 --> 22:32.852
- [grunting]

22:32.987 --> 22:36.722
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:36.724 --> 22:37.857
Hold him, hold him.

22:37.992 --> 22:39.591
Ahh. Open up.

22:39.727 --> 22:41.793
- [groans]

22:41.795 --> 22:43.395
- Ahh!

22:43.531 --> 22:46.932
- [grunting]

22:47.068 --> 22:49.669
[air hisses]

22:49.803 --> 22:54.073
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:56.878 --> 22:59.144
- Look, even if we catch up
with him,

22:59.280 --> 23:00.812
we still have
the harpoon issue,

23:00.948 --> 23:02.081
and we can't connect
end to end.

23:02.216 --> 23:04.950
We'll never overpower
his Jackboots.

23:04.952 --> 23:06.352
- No.

23:06.487 --> 23:08.420
- No.

23:08.556 --> 23:11.223
So we need a plan
to get into his engine.

23:11.225 --> 23:13.159
We need a distraction.

23:14.362 --> 23:15.294
- Audrey.

23:15.429 --> 23:22.134
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:26.440 --> 23:28.240
- What's this?

23:28.242 --> 23:29.508
- Hands behind your back.

23:29.643 --> 23:33.045
- Ooh, handcuffs.
I knew you had a kink.

23:34.716 --> 23:36.549
- Move.
- Mmm.

23:38.586 --> 23:39.851
- Good luck.

23:39.987 --> 23:42.854
<i> [ominous music]</i>

23:42.990 --> 23:47.859
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:47.861 --> 23:50.329
- It's moody in here.

23:50.464 --> 23:51.931
- Sit.

23:55.803 --> 23:57.669
- How much further?

23:57.805 --> 23:58.938
- We're almost at the ridge,

23:59.073 --> 24:01.340
but we're basically
running on fumes.

24:01.475 --> 24:04.510
- Keep pushing. She'll make it.
Then we're home free.

24:08.750 --> 24:10.082
- Nice and easy, Ben.

24:10.217 --> 24:17.323
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:20.894 --> 24:22.694
- Joseph.

24:22.696 --> 24:29.635
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:32.774 --> 24:35.675
[metal screeches]

24:37.511 --> 24:40.780
<i> - Big Alice,</i>
<i> this is Snowpiercer.</i>

24:40.914 --> 24:42.081
<i> Come in.</i>

24:45.519 --> 24:47.453
<i> Snowpiercer to Big Alice,</i>
<i> come in.</i>

24:47.455 --> 24:49.522
- Sir, should--should I answer?
- No, no.

24:54.128 --> 24:55.795
- Come in, Big Alice.

24:55.929 --> 25:01.333
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:01.335 --> 25:04.403
- This is Big Alice.
To whom am I speaking?

25:04.538 --> 25:08.474
- I'm the guy standing between
you and open track, Wilford.

25:08.610 --> 25:10.476
- I see that.

25:10.612 --> 25:12.678
So it's a game of chicken,
is it?

25:12.814 --> 25:14.079
- At the rate you're going,
I don't think

25:14.215 --> 25:15.615
you'll make it this far.

25:15.749 --> 25:19.485
- Oh, Big Alice has more fight
than you know.

25:20.354 --> 25:22.154
<i> You called this meeting,</i>
<i> Layton.</i>

25:23.957 --> 25:25.491
So go on,

25:25.493 --> 25:28.694
or are we just gonna stand here
pissing off our prows?

25:29.897 --> 25:32.231
- When we left, we made a deal.

25:32.366 --> 25:33.965
<i> I keep Audrey safe--</i>

25:33.967 --> 25:36.368
<i> - I remember,</i>
<i> and I don't murder everyone.</i>

25:36.504 --> 25:37.703
Yes, I remember the deal.

25:37.839 --> 25:41.240
It was made under duress,
I'll remind you.

25:41.375 --> 25:42.842
But I stuck to it.

25:42.976 --> 25:44.577
- Where's Zarah?

25:47.781 --> 25:49.248
- She's right here.

25:49.383 --> 25:51.851
[chuckles]
Positively glowing.

25:51.986 --> 25:54.320
<i> - I'm here, Andre. I'm okay.</i>

25:55.389 --> 25:57.256
- And Audrey?

25:57.391 --> 25:59.425
I want to hear her.

26:02.997 --> 26:05.164
I need to know she's all right.

26:07.735 --> 26:10.636
<i> - Surrender the train</i>
<i> and you can tell her yourself.</i>

26:13.207 --> 26:14.674
- Surrender?

26:14.808 --> 26:17.877
<i> - We'll give you a car</i>
<i> in First, food, drink.</i>

26:18.012 --> 26:21.813
You two can live out
your years together.

26:21.815 --> 26:23.815
- So I--

26:23.817 --> 26:26.285
I give you
absolutely everything,

26:26.420 --> 26:28.954
and you give me
a little piece back in return?

26:29.090 --> 26:30.690
That's quite some offer,
Layton.

26:30.824 --> 26:34.494
- The offer is,
we end this without violence,

26:34.628 --> 26:38.497
or you could roll back down
into that rail yard

26:38.632 --> 26:40.099
<i> and we'll pick you apart.</i>

26:40.234 --> 26:41.701
- That's it, sir. We're tapped.

26:41.835 --> 26:45.771
[engines whir]

26:45.773 --> 26:47.373
- No deal.

26:54.848 --> 26:57.717
<i> [dark, emotional music]</i>

26:57.851 --> 27:04.490
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:05.659 --> 27:10.163
I...I want to hear her voice.

27:24.278 --> 27:25.877
- Joseph.

27:26.013 --> 27:33.119
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:47.435 --> 27:48.968
- All right, Ben,
I'm at the cold-Lock.

27:49.103 --> 27:56.275
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:00.848 --> 28:03.783
- Soon, soon.
[rumbling]

28:03.917 --> 28:10.790
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:14.395 --> 28:15.995
- Auto-engaging hot reverse.

28:16.130 --> 28:19.198
We should switch helms and get
Big Alice pushing again.

28:19.333 --> 28:21.634
- Full stop, Engineer.

28:22.470 --> 28:24.270
Let her power down.

28:24.405 --> 28:25.937
- What?
- Joseph.

28:25.939 --> 28:28.874
<i> [tense music]</i>

28:29.010 --> 28:30.209
[metal screeching]

28:30.344 --> 28:31.644
[people gasping]

28:33.147 --> 28:35.848
- That can't be good, can it?

28:37.018 --> 28:38.884
- No.

28:39.020 --> 28:42.888
- Snowpiercer, we are dead
on the tracks.

28:42.890 --> 28:47.426
If you don't reconnect,
everyone will freeze to death.

28:47.561 --> 28:54.033
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:54.168 --> 28:55.735
- You're desperate.

28:56.838 --> 28:58.604
- And you have no choice.

29:03.377 --> 29:05.777
- Prepare to connect.

29:05.779 --> 29:09.916
Javi,<i> abre una cerveza, amigo.</i>

29:11.585 --> 29:15.120
- Commander,
move your boarding party

29:15.122 --> 29:16.822
to the connection point.

29:18.059 --> 29:19.458
- Generation deficit.

29:19.593 --> 29:21.927
Train-wide temperature
is dropping right now.

29:22.063 --> 29:24.196
- Better get your woolies on.

29:24.332 --> 29:26.566
- All right, boys, you ready?

29:27.935 --> 29:29.335
- Move out.

29:29.470 --> 29:31.270
[indistinct]
Remember where to aim.

29:31.405 --> 29:33.539
- They're preparing to dock.

29:35.076 --> 29:36.676
- They've got no choice.

29:36.810 --> 29:38.344
- [indistinct shouting]
Let's go, let's go.

29:38.346 --> 29:40.012
Move, move, move.

29:40.014 --> 29:41.413
- Cap okay?

29:41.549 --> 29:43.883
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

29:44.018 --> 29:46.752
- Hey, watch your back.
Move it, move it!

29:49.490 --> 29:51.290
- This is crazy, Ben.

29:51.425 --> 29:53.158
- Yeah, pirate's life.

29:53.160 --> 29:55.361
- Shit.
- You're all right.

29:55.496 --> 29:58.163
Just reverse her in
as fast as you dare.

29:58.165 --> 29:59.599
- Shit.

30:00.968 --> 30:03.703
- And don't reconnect
until we're in position.

30:03.837 --> 30:06.505
[rumbling]

30:06.640 --> 30:10.842
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:10.844 --> 30:13.645
- Hey, remember, people,
we're gonna clear it first.

30:13.647 --> 30:16.181
- Weapons ready? Move!

30:16.317 --> 30:23.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:26.394 --> 30:28.327
- Christ.

30:28.462 --> 30:31.731
Josephine. She's back.

30:33.067 --> 30:35.301
The bloody balls.

30:38.672 --> 30:41.140
Did you climb aboard,
you little hobo?

30:41.275 --> 30:42.674
[laughs]

30:42.810 --> 30:45.378
Uh-uh, baby on board.

30:46.547 --> 30:49.681
No, you won't.

30:49.817 --> 30:51.216
She won't.
[bangs on glass]

30:51.218 --> 30:52.652
[shouts]

30:56.357 --> 30:58.991
Damn. Good one.

31:00.161 --> 31:01.861
- [grunts]
- Ahh!

31:04.298 --> 31:06.966
[both grunting]

31:07.101 --> 31:09.034
- [screams]

31:09.170 --> 31:16.041
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:16.177 --> 31:18.978
[grunting]

31:19.113 --> 31:26.085
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:30.391 --> 31:32.992
- Tell your men to stand down

31:33.127 --> 31:35.595
or I will throw you
off this train.

31:36.664 --> 31:39.264
- [breathing heavily]

31:39.266 --> 31:42.267
<i> [tense music]</i>

31:42.269 --> 31:44.470
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:44.606 --> 31:46.439
[bell dings]

31:49.010 --> 31:51.511
- This is
Head Engineer Wilford.

31:52.614 --> 31:54.780
<i> Boarding party, stand down.</i>

31:56.350 --> 32:00.219
[both sighing]

32:00.354 --> 32:04.289
<i> We will not be taking...</i>

32:04.291 --> 32:06.025
<i> Snowpiercer by force.</i>

32:06.160 --> 32:08.094
[indistinct chatter]

32:10.764 --> 32:12.865
<i> Stand down. Weapons down.</i>

32:14.302 --> 32:16.368
- Oh, my God.

32:16.504 --> 32:23.609
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:26.848 --> 32:29.381
- Happy now?

32:29.517 --> 32:31.150
- Say it!

32:42.396 --> 32:46.766
- Andre Layton has the train.

32:50.404 --> 32:53.205
- Citizens of Snowpiercer...

32:53.207 --> 32:59.411
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:59.547 --> 33:01.414
We're back.

33:05.486 --> 33:07.152
[sighs]

33:07.288 --> 33:13.993
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:26.574 --> 33:29.975
50 meters, 40 meters,

33:30.111 --> 33:32.511
25 meters...
[monitors beeping]

33:32.646 --> 33:36.582
[engine whirs]

33:36.584 --> 33:39.752
[rumbling]

33:42.856 --> 33:44.924
- It can't be just over.

33:45.059 --> 33:48.728
<i> [Barry McGuire's</i>
<i> "Eve of Destruction"]</i>

33:48.862 --> 33:50.529
- Well, I think it's about time

33:50.664 --> 33:53.532
we get on
the right side of history.

33:53.667 --> 33:58.204
<i> - ♪ The Eastern world,</i>
<i> it is explodin' ♪</i>

33:58.339 --> 34:02.074
<i> ♪ Violence flarin',</i>
<i> bullets loadin' ♪</i>

34:02.209 --> 34:04.610
<i> ♪ You're old enough to kill ♪</i>

34:04.746 --> 34:06.278
- Here you go.

34:06.280 --> 34:08.280
<i> - ♪ You don't believe in war ♪</i>

34:08.416 --> 34:10.215
<i> ♪ But what's that gun</i>
<i> you're totin'?</i>

34:10.217 --> 34:13.152
- [sighs]

34:13.287 --> 34:16.888
Oz, I love you so much.

34:17.024 --> 34:22.094
<i> - ♪ Over and over</i>
<i> and over again, my friend ♪</i>

34:22.229 --> 34:25.030
- [gasps]

34:25.166 --> 34:27.299
[spluttering]

34:27.435 --> 34:30.102
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

34:30.237 --> 34:33.172
<i> - ♪ Oh, no,</i>
<i> you don't believe ♪</i>

34:33.307 --> 34:36.375
<i> ♪ We're on the eve</i>
<i> of destruction ♪</i>

34:36.510 --> 34:37.909
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:37.911 --> 34:40.112
- Long live the Resistance!

34:40.247 --> 34:43.583
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:47.822 --> 34:50.889
<i> [emotional music]</i>

34:51.025 --> 34:57.896
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:58.032 --> 35:00.432
[people cheering]

35:00.568 --> 35:03.702
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:03.838 --> 35:05.304
[cheers and applause]

35:05.439 --> 35:06.705
- Bottom's up.

35:06.707 --> 35:09.842
[keys jingling]

35:14.314 --> 35:15.848
- [exhales]

35:15.984 --> 35:22.922
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:27.662 --> 35:29.127
- Ah, found it.

35:29.129 --> 35:30.630
- Ruth?

35:32.200 --> 35:33.765
- Andre.

35:34.802 --> 35:37.135
- I never would have found you.
You're in civvies.

35:37.137 --> 35:38.471
- [chuckles]

35:39.674 --> 35:42.208
I remembered that Wilford had
a secret tipple up here.

35:42.343 --> 35:44.543
- Oh, could use some of that.
- Wanna celebrate?

35:44.679 --> 35:46.345
- Yes.

35:46.480 --> 35:48.747
- Oh, welcome home.

35:48.749 --> 35:51.184
It's good to have you back.

35:52.820 --> 35:55.087
- I knew you'd hold
everyone together.

35:55.089 --> 35:56.589
Well done.

35:59.293 --> 36:00.626
- Let's do it.

36:00.761 --> 36:02.428
- Take them out.

36:06.500 --> 36:08.167
- He's stable.

36:10.104 --> 36:11.904
[beeping]

36:13.774 --> 36:16.042
Carly's stable.

36:16.176 --> 36:17.509
And Anne--

36:17.645 --> 36:20.646
[alarms beeping]

36:20.781 --> 36:22.114
[gasps]

36:22.116 --> 36:25.183
<i> [somber music]</i>

36:25.319 --> 36:31.590
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:31.726 --> 36:34.593
[rumbling]

36:34.729 --> 36:41.834
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:50.278 --> 36:52.678
[indistinct chatter]

36:52.813 --> 36:59.986
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:08.629 --> 37:11.497
- [sobbing]

37:11.632 --> 37:13.666
- Javi.

37:24.779 --> 37:27.446
Hey.
- [shudders]

37:27.581 --> 37:34.453
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:34.588 --> 37:36.255
- Oh, man.

37:37.792 --> 37:40.993
- [sobbing]

37:42.997 --> 37:46.532
- This warm spot,
the Horn of Africa,

37:46.667 --> 37:48.600
you really believe
it can support life?

37:48.602 --> 37:50.336
- Yeah, our future
is there, Ruth.

37:50.471 --> 37:52.205
I believe it with all my heart.

37:53.942 --> 37:56.342
- You know, the Horn of Africa,
the approach is maybe

37:56.477 --> 37:58.276
the worst stretch of track
on the entire network.

37:58.278 --> 38:00.346
And there was a war there
when the climate crashed.

38:00.481 --> 38:02.081
- Yeah, yeah, I remember.

38:03.083 --> 38:04.416
- The people are tired, Andre.

38:04.552 --> 38:06.218
It's been a long six months,
and your first order

38:06.354 --> 38:08.554
is gonna be to steer them
right back into more hardship?

38:08.689 --> 38:09.822
- Mm-mmm,
there won't be an order.

38:09.824 --> 38:12.291
We'll put it to a vote.

38:12.426 --> 38:14.026
- A vote?
- Yeah.

38:14.028 --> 38:16.028
We'll show them
that democracy has won.

38:16.164 --> 38:18.230
We'll choose
our path forward together.

38:19.167 --> 38:21.033
- And you're prepared
for the outcome of this vote?

38:21.169 --> 38:24.903
- I am going to convince them
that it is worth the risk.

38:24.905 --> 38:27.173
Snowpiercer's running
on duct tape and prayers.

38:27.307 --> 38:29.942
This is a real opportunity
to get off.

38:31.712 --> 38:34.046
- It's also a vote
on you, Andre.

38:34.182 --> 38:36.983
Much of the train doesn't
support your leadership.

38:37.117 --> 38:39.252
- This isn't just about me.

38:40.655 --> 38:42.855
It's what Melanie
would have wanted.

38:43.924 --> 38:47.660
- All right.
I'll, uh, inform the notary.

38:47.795 --> 38:50.196
I know that everyone aboard
will take their vote to heart,

38:50.330 --> 38:53.866
but are you prepared
to accept it if they vote no?

38:56.404 --> 38:57.803
You better think long and hard

38:57.938 --> 39:00.206
about exactly what it is
you're gonna tell them.

39:00.341 --> 39:03.209
<i> [tense music]</i>

39:03.344 --> 39:08.681
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:08.683 --> 39:12.218
- You're confined to Third
and barred from the Nightcar.

39:12.353 --> 39:13.686
- Where's Joseph?

39:13.688 --> 39:14.953
- You picked the wrong side,
Audrey.

39:14.955 --> 39:18.090
- Traitor. Walk away.

39:18.226 --> 39:19.625
- Has there ever been
a right side

39:19.760 --> 39:21.060
on this goddamn train?

39:23.097 --> 39:25.431
It's all gonna go to shit.
You'll see.

39:25.566 --> 39:31.437
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:31.572 --> 39:33.272
- [winces in pain]

39:35.243 --> 39:37.376
[groans]

39:39.247 --> 39:42.715
- It went
straight through my hand.

39:42.850 --> 39:46.318
- Something to remember us by.

39:46.320 --> 39:47.853
- Look at you.

39:47.988 --> 39:50.823
A monster come for its creator.

39:52.260 --> 39:54.360
[chuckles]
- It's poetic, isn't it?

39:57.398 --> 40:00.066
- Layton can't hold it
together, you know.

40:01.201 --> 40:03.236
They'll reject him again.

40:05.073 --> 40:07.339
I am the train.

40:07.341 --> 40:14.313
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:20.488 --> 40:22.821
- A vote?

40:22.823 --> 40:24.190
- That's right.

40:25.760 --> 40:28.226
You'll get a vote today too.

40:28.362 --> 40:30.362
- [laughs]

40:30.364 --> 40:31.830
Politics.

40:31.832 --> 40:33.031
You forget about them

40:33.167 --> 40:35.101
when you're
the last person on Earth.

40:36.905 --> 40:38.837
Thank you.

40:38.839 --> 40:40.973
- Don't thank me just yet.

40:41.109 --> 40:42.975
There's something
I need to ask of you.

40:44.512 --> 40:47.046
- You brought me
back to life, Andre.

40:50.050 --> 40:53.085
What is it?

40:56.623 --> 40:59.224
<i> [Bonobo's "Grains"]</i>

40:59.360 --> 41:02.427
<i> [soft atmospheric music]</i>

41:02.563 --> 41:09.468
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:25.786 --> 41:27.452
[bell dings]

41:27.454 --> 41:29.021
- Shh. Shh.

41:32.994 --> 41:35.294
- My fellow passengers...

41:37.332 --> 41:39.131
Today,

41:39.266 --> 41:43.468
for the first time
since our departure...

41:43.604 --> 41:47.540
you will have a say
in our destination,

41:47.675 --> 41:50.009
and your choice
will determine our future.

41:50.011 --> 41:51.344
<i> By now, you know</i>

41:51.478 --> 41:54.880
<i> that Melanie's sacrifice</i>
<i> gave us a map.</i>

41:54.882 --> 41:59.284
<i> Proof that there are places</i>
<i> on the Earth that are warming.</i>

41:59.420 --> 42:03.689
<i> Traveling fast and light,</i>
<i> we tested each of them.</i>

42:03.691 --> 42:06.892
<i> Sulawesi, Gujarat,</i>

42:07.028 --> 42:11.096
<i> Managua, the Atacama.</i>

42:11.232 --> 42:13.966
<i> And each one of these</i>
<i> let us down.</i>

42:14.101 --> 42:18.303
<i> I know that you have</i>
<i> suffered badly</i>

42:18.305 --> 42:21.374
<i> because of our decision</i>
<i> to break the train.</i>

42:21.508 --> 42:23.242
<i> But there is one more location</i>

42:23.378 --> 42:26.912
<i> on which I ask you</i>
<i> to stake your hope:</i>

42:27.048 --> 42:29.582
<i> the Horn of Africa.</i>

42:29.717 --> 42:32.317
<i> The journey to return there</i>
<i> will be fraught with risk</i>

42:32.319 --> 42:34.587
<i> and the hardships</i>
<i> will continue,</i>

42:34.722 --> 42:39.926
but we have someone here
who can renew our faith.

42:42.329 --> 42:44.730
Someone we had given up
on believing in.

42:44.865 --> 42:51.971
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:53.274 --> 42:55.007
- What's he doing?

42:55.142 --> 42:57.943
<i> - But I'll let her tell you.</i>

42:57.945 --> 42:59.678
- He's bullshitting.

42:59.680 --> 43:06.652
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:11.826 --> 43:14.427
- My name is Asha.

43:15.630 --> 43:18.230
<i> I am a survivor.</i>

43:18.365 --> 43:23.035
<i> Layton found me out there,</i>
<i> outside.</i>

43:23.170 --> 43:25.838
<i> Along with trees,</i>

43:25.973 --> 43:28.974
<i> green grass...</i>

43:29.110 --> 43:30.610
<i> and life.</i>

43:33.848 --> 43:37.250
I come from New Eden.

43:37.384 --> 43:42.254
<i> - ♪ One ♪</i>

43:42.389 --> 43:44.790
<i> ♪ Grain of sand ♪</i>

43:44.925 --> 43:48.527
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:48.663 --> 43:52.932
<i> ♪ Ah ♪</i>

43:53.067 --> 43:56.935
<i> ♪ Water in the sea ♪</i>

43:56.937 --> 44:01.407
<i> - I'm not asking you to choose</i>
<i> between me and Wilford.</i>

44:02.943 --> 44:06.812
<i> I am asking you to choose</i>
<i> between the train we know</i>

44:06.947 --> 44:09.214
<i> and the dream we don't.</i>

44:09.350 --> 44:12.685
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:12.820 --> 44:16.155
<i> Thank you all so much</i>
<i> for your sacrifices.</i>

44:16.157 --> 44:21.626
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:21.628 --> 44:24.463
The story needed a hero,
and we brought one back.

44:25.500 --> 44:28.233
- Well, in the wake
of that performance,

44:28.235 --> 44:29.968
the yeas have it.

44:29.970 --> 44:31.337
Almost two to one.

44:33.308 --> 44:34.773
- What's one more lie?

44:34.775 --> 44:36.842
- The difference is,
this is the last one

44:36.844 --> 44:37.776
we will have to tell.

44:37.912 --> 44:39.444
- Well, I doubt that.

44:39.446 --> 44:43.182
I've come to think
this train demands a lie.

44:43.184 --> 44:44.517
- Yeah,

44:44.651 --> 44:48.387
like an imaginary genius
in the engine.

44:48.389 --> 44:51.390
- Or Melanie saving us
with perfect science.

44:51.526 --> 44:55.661
- Or a survivor
to show us the way.

44:55.796 --> 44:58.998
- So...we press on.

44:59.000 --> 45:00.399
- Agreed.

45:00.401 --> 45:02.301
- What else are we gonna do?

45:03.670 --> 45:04.737
- Josie?

45:06.207 --> 45:07.940
- Well, we better be right.

45:08.075 --> 45:13.078
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:13.214 --> 45:15.348
<i> [bells ding]</i>

45:15.482 --> 45:19.552
<i> - Fellow passengers,</i>
<i> our great endeavor continues.</i>

45:19.687 --> 45:23.356
<i> You have spoken,</i>
<i> and by majority rule,</i>

45:23.490 --> 45:26.291
<i> we are heading for New Eden.</i>

45:26.293 --> 45:28.027
[breathing echoes]

45:28.162 --> 45:31.030
<i> [ominous music]</i>

45:31.165 --> 45:34.367
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

45:38.172 --> 45:40.172
<i> [intense music]</i>

45:40.307 --> 45:47.380
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
